BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.040 0.340 0.780 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 754.00 Tm (SAY \(read this aloud\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 738.00 Tm (So what exactly is JDBC? Let me explain it in plain language first, and then we will look at the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 722.80 Tm (three points on screen.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 702.60 Tm (JDBC is a set of rules - a standard way - that Java gives us for talking to databases. Now here is) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 687.40 Tm (the clever part, and the first card says it: JDBC is mostly just interfaces. Remember from your Java) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 672.20 Tm (classes, an interface is like a contract - it says what methods must exist, but it does not say how) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 657.00 Tm (they actually work. JDBC lives in a package called java dot s-q-l, and it defines things like 'there) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 641.80 Tm (must be a way to open a connection' and 'there must be a way to run a query' - but it does not) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 626.60 Tm (write the actual code for any specific database.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 606.40 Tm (So who writes the real code? That is the second card. The database company - Oracle, MySQL,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 591.20 Tm (and so on - writes it for us and ships it as a JAR file. We call that JAR file the driver. One) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 576.00 Tm (database, one driver.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 555.80 Tm (Let me give you a simple analogy. Think of JDBC like a universal power socket on the wall. The) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 540.60 Tm (socket has a standard shape - that is the interface. Different appliances - a fan, a charger, a lamp -) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 525.40 Tm (each have their own plug that fits that same socket. The database driver is like the plug for one) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 510.20 Tm (specific appliance. Your Java code just talks to the socket, and it does not care which appliance is) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 495.00 Tm (plugged in.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 474.80 Tm (And the third card is the big-picture reason this matters: every modern tool - Hibernate, JPA,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 459.60 Tm (Spring Data - all of them sit on top of JDBC. They just write these JDBC calls for you behind the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 444.40 Tm (scenes.) Tj ET
0.040 0.520 1.000 rg 58.00 429.20 3.00 330.80 re f
