BT /F1 10.50 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 402.20 Tm (Land the punchline from the key box: because your code only talks to the interface, you can switch) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 387.80 Tm (from MySQL to Oracle by changing the driver and the URL - your actual logic does not change. That is) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 373.40 Tm (the whole power of interface-based design, and it is a great interview answer.) Tj ET
