BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 754.00 Tm (Second, the Connection. This represents one open conversation with the database. And here is) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 738.80 Tm (something important - opening a connection is expensive. It opens a real network line to the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 723.60 Tm (database, like making a phone call. So just like a phone call, you must hang up when you are) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 708.40 Tm (done. We always close the connection.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 688.20 Tm (Third, the PreparedStatement. This is the object that actually carries your SQL query to the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 673.00 Tm (database. It is the safe, modern way to do it, and we will spend a lot of time on why it is safe.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 652.80 Tm (And fourth, the ResultSet. When you ask the database to find something, it does not hand you all) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 637.60 Tm (the rows at once. Instead it gives you a ResultSet, which is like a cursor or a pointer that walks) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 622.40 Tm (through the results one row at a time.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 602.20 Tm (So picture them as a chain: the DriverManager gives you a Connection; from the Connection you) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 587.00 Tm (make a PreparedStatement; and running that statement gives you a ResultSet to read. Door,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 571.80 Tm (conversation, question, answer. That chain is the backbone of everything we do today.) Tj ET
