BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 434.60 Tm (Alright, this slide is the recipe. If you remember nothing else from today, remember these five) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 419.40 Tm (steps, because every single JDBC program - whether it inserts, reads, updates, or deletes -) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 404.20 Tm (follows exactly this shape. Let me walk you through it like a cooking recipe.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 384.00 Tm (Step one: register the driver, using Class dot forName. Honestly, in modern Java this happens) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 368.80 Tm (automatically, but we show it so you understand it is happening. Think of it as telling Java, 'hey,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 353.60 Tm (get the right driver ready'.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 333.40 Tm (Step two: open the connection, using DriverManager dot getConnection. You pass the address,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 318.20 Tm (the username, and the password. This is where we pick up the phone and dial the database.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 298.00 Tm (Step three: prepare your statement. You write your SQL and hand it to the connection. Now the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 282.80 Tm (question is ready to ask.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 262.60 Tm (Step four: execute. You run it. If you are reading data, you use executeQuery; if you are changing) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 247.40 Tm (data, you use executeUpdate. We will look at that difference very soon.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 227.20 Tm (And step five - and please never forget this one - close the connection. Release the resource.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 212.00 Tm (Hang up the phone.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 191.80 Tm (So just to recap the recipe: register, connect, prepare, execute, close. Five steps. Say it with me a) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 176.60 Tm (couple of times during the lab and it will become automatic.) Tj ET
