BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 393.60 Tm (The first question mark is position one. Java is usually zero-based, but here it is one-based, so just) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 378.40 Tm (keep that in mind.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 358.20 Tm (The three cards sum up why PreparedStatement wins: it is faster, because the database) Tj ET
