BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 577.20 Tm (walk through.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 557.00 Tm (Use executeUpdate when you are changing something - that is INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 541.80 Tm (also creating tables. Changing data does not give you back rows; instead it gives you back a) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 526.60 Tm (single number - how many rows were affected.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 506.40 Tm (Here is the easy way to remember it: 'Query' has the word for asking a question - reading. 'Update') Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 491.20 Tm (is about changing - writing. Reading returns data, changing returns a count.) Tj ET
