BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 490.20 Tm (Remember I told you a connection is like a phone call, and you must always hang up? Well, this) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 475.00 Tm (slide is about making sure you never forget to hang up - even when something goes wrong.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 454.80 Tm (Here is the danger. Suppose you open a connection, and then halfway through your code an error) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 439.60 Tm (is thrown. The program jumps away to handle the error, and your close line never runs. The) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 424.40 Tm (connection stays open forever. We call that a leak. And if your application leaks connections all) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 409.20 Tm (day, eventually the database runs out and the whole system grinds to a halt.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 389.00 Tm (Look at the left panel - that is the old way of being safe. You use a finally block, with null checks,) Tj ET
