BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 323.20 Tm (Java now promises to automatically close them for you - whether your code finishes happily or) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 308.00 Tm (whether an error is thrown. You literally cannot forget, because Java does it for you.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 287.80 Tm (So the rule is simple: anything that needs closing - connections, statements, result sets - put it in) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 272.60 Tm (the try brackets, and let Java handle the cleanup. From now on, this is how we write all our) Tj ET
