BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.040 0.340 0.780 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 388.90 Tm (SAY \(read this aloud\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 372.90 Tm (Some of you might be thinking, 'if Spring does all this for me, why am I learning JDBC by hand?') Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 357.70 Tm (That is a fair question, so let me answer it honestly with this comparison.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 337.50 Tm (With raw JDBC - what we are learning today - you write a fair amount of code. You write the SQL) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 322.30 Tm (yourself and you map the results by hand. The upside is total control: you can write any query you) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 307.10 Tm (can imagine. And the learning curve is gentle - it is really just SQL plus the four interfaces we met.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 286.90 Tm (With Spring Data JPA, you write very little code - often just a method name, and Spring writes the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 271.70 Tm (query for you. It is wonderfully fast to build with. But the trade-off is that you need to learn quite a) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 256.50 Tm (few JPA concepts first, so the learning curve is steeper.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 236.30 Tm (So which is better? Neither - they are for different situations. JDBC shines for legacy systems and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 221.10 Tm (for complex, hand-tuned queries. JPA shines for most everyday modern applications.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 200.90 Tm (But here is the real reason you are learning JDBC first. You learn JDBC to understand the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 185.70 Tm (foundation - to see what is really happening. Then you use JPA to build quickly on top of that) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 170.50 Tm (understanding. A person who only knows JPA gets stuck the moment something goes wrong) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 155.30 Tm (underneath. You will not, because you will know what is going on.) Tj ET
